    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Ninhydrin gives yellow colour in paper chromatography with which amino acid?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Tryptophan"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Proline"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "Alanine"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Tyrosine"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Option B :\nProline</p>\n<p>Explanation :</p>\n<p>Ninhydrin is a chemical reagent commonly used to detect amino acids, peptides, and proteins. While most amino acids react with ninhydrin to give a purple-blue color, Proline and hydroxyproline are exceptions. These two amino acids react with ninhydrin to give a yellow color instead. This is because proline is a secondary amino acid, meaning its amino group is a part of a ring structure, which alters its reactivity compared to primary amino acids.</p>\n",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "bitsat-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
